  "directions": {
    "base": [
      "In a medium saucepan, combine corn kernels, water, sugar, and salt. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.",
      "Reduce heat to medium and simmer for 10-15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until corn is tender and most of the liquid has evaporated.",
      "Remove from heat and stir in vanilla extract. Let cool completely.",
      "In a small bowl, whisk together sweetened condensed milk and evaporated milk until smooth.",
      "To serve, fill 4 glasses or bowls with shaved ice.",
      "Top each portion of ice with 1/2 cup of the cooled corn mixture.",
      "Drizzle each serving with the milk mixture.",
      "Sprinkle with ground cinnamon and serve immediately with spoons."
